Here we describe the human-robot dynamic interaction for two degree of freedom planar movement (Fig. 1a). We employed established methods of inverse dynamics of upper limb motion to estimate the elbow and shoulder joint torques generated by the human. This analysis considers the human arm as a closed system where an external force at the wrist is available from the force sensor measurements. Thus, the model considers the influence of the torques acting on each joint; including, the torque required to move the arm passively (τp) which is composed of the torque generated by the human (τh) and the torque acting on the arm by the robot (τr). The passive load of the arm can be expressed as \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
